The adventure starts off very well.
You're caught up in an adventure where the main character Jack has a personality problem and to solve it, he starts to participate in illegal racing across America.
You sit behind the wheel on the West Coast in San Francisco and your mission is to get to New York first.
There are some interesting elements to the idea.
The route is divided into ten stages and then more than 50 races.
The result is that each race is run on a different route and the stages are planned in different environments which are quite distinct from each other and are interesting.
The player does not have the feeling for a single moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are also quite beautiful even if the graphic level is the same as in the previous series.
It's not the end of the world.
