The problem is that in more extreme situations, the imagery doesn't hold up, and in some cases tragically.
This is especially true of accidents with a large number of participants when a fluid image is no longer of any use to you.
The sound is good, and the track is optional.
In order to appeal to the widest possible audience, and especially the youngest, a new soundtrack was created in the "I mix everything" style, but one can expect that no one will buy the game for the music.
