The students of velvet in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that link International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival, 20 choirs from high schools and secondary schools perform.
The highlight of the festival is two concerts on 17 November.
"Charles University has a big part in this festival".
"Among the choirs is the Choir of the Faculty of Education and Humanities, and the festival committee is headed by the rector Vaclav Hampl", says the head of the organizing team, Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the concert of the Choir of High Schools and Secondary Schools which takes place with free entry on November 17 from 2 pm on the space in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the program is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening, the "Students of Velvet" concert takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady, during which the choirs of the higher schools and the one of Charles University perform.
The Festa Academica aims not only to celebrate the International Students' Day with dignity and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present the public with choir music of the highest level and to develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organiser is the Czech Choir Union in cooperation with the Jan Kepler High School.
The whole project is under the auspices of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague, and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The programme also offers high-level concerts, musical meetings, a student happening and other activities.
All information can be found on the festival's website www.festaacademica.cz.
