History of a brand
The innovative IBM begins its second century
If one were to look for the word that most closely expresses IBM's strategy, the closest would be "the long term".
For a large audience, IBM is the symbol of the technological revolution, a firm that is felt to be very modern and yet a hundred years have passed since its creation.
The foundation for this long-term strategy was laid by the firm's first CEO, the visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left behind this slogan that a great many of the world's problems can be solved if people are willing to think.
His slogan "THINK!" became the imprint around which the life of a future giant would develop (and also the title of the in-house magazine that IBM began publishing in 1935).
It was the basis of the corporate healthcare culture developed by Watson.
For us, IBM means thinking long term, moving forward.
IBM has survived a hundred years because it has always remained true to its core values and yet has not been afraid to change everyone else around it.
It has allowed us in our first century to transform technology, business and society.
We hope that in the second century we will achieve even more", said the firm's current director Samuel J. Palmisano.
A well-prepared system
Watson, in the 1930s, began to take care of his employees like Bata in the Czech Republic - IBM people were the only among the first American employees to have paid holidays, employer-paid insurance plus an elegant employee uniform and a well-developed system of rewards for inventors and merchants.
Similarly, IBM has a well-developed customer relationship system.
The company was great at the beginning in finding talent - as one of the first firms to have abolished all forms of discrimination and thus had a choice.
The current plan is completely in the spirit of the anti-discrimination strategy as it will be a woman - Virginia Rometty - who is expected to replace Palmisano at the helm of IBM.
She has been with IBM for thirty years and is currently Head of Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
IBM has been doing what's called jamy over the last few years, online brainstorming, and a lot of future strategies and innovations have come out of that.
It's no wonder he has a lot of ideas - there are almost 500,000 people working in the firm.
An institution with a good name
The internal and external image of the company is what gives it a secure position in the business world.
