Facebook also constantly accesses the information of its users.
The site's data team looked at statistics on love and Valentine's Day, turnout in the 2010 midterm elections, and a national happiness index (through only available information - digital freedom champions have long argued that the site could make its treasure trove of data available to others for research purposes).
