With the demise of the CMB in 1987, the park became again, in the imagination of many people, the upper limit of Barcelona, the Catalan capital being the only one that does not orientate on the north-south axis, otherwise up (mountain) - down (sea).
The designation of Collserola as a nature park is a favourable idea.
The reference was no longer Central Park but Yellowstone, with wild boars in the role of Yogi bear.
This was the case until the city council held a 16-man mega-competition in September for all the access gates to Collserola.
A door that reminds you of a park, no doubt.
That, or someone wants to put doors on the field.
