Bayona insinuates that the answer to the question giving the title of this piece is complex, because the basics of the competition lack a global vision of Collserola: "We have called 16 cross-sectional competitions - he says - in the direction of mountain-sea, but there is no longitudinal reading that sees and understands the area as a whole".
This is at least in this case, since he has chosen to participate in all 16 competitions.
In other words, a project so that one of the doors can clash in program and definition with that of the architect of the next door.
In his opinion, yes, the city should ensure that the strip immediately above that of Ronda de Dalt should provide, throughout its extension, a facility area which makes a smooth transition between the city and the green.
Casino forgives Jons Larrazbal and he will be released
