The microblogging site Twitter on Monday introduced changes to the presentation of its platform, including allowing users to observe the activity of those they follow, making its service a bit more similar to Facebook.
A new "activity" tab and another "name" allow you to follow more easily, live, the activity of other "Twittos", the users whose messages ("tweets") you follow and those who follow you.
